main event: A civilian observed a round, teardrop-shaped object in the sky while walking to work on 4 April 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3 to 4 minutes from a distance of about 1.5 miles east of Holly, Florida., The object emitted a very high-pitched sound as it ascended, similar to a high-velocity wind machine., The observer described the object's color as grey, with brushed aluminum texture., The object rose slowly to approximately 90 feet and then moved rapidly to the west before disappearing almost instantaneously., The report indicated insufficient data for evaluation, and no physical evidence was found.
witness description: civilian, age 49, service station general store operator from Gainesville, Florida
